TITLE: Creating a Type-Specific Identity Function in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: A simple identity function with a specific number type that returns whatever argument is passed to it. This demonstrates a non-generic approach with a fixed type.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/typescript-website/blob/v2/packages/documentation/copy/en/handbook-v2/Type Manipulation/Generics.md#2025-04-20_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
function identity(arg: number): number {
  return arg;
}
```

