TITLE: Problematic Optional Parameters in Callbacks
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates a common mistake when defining callbacks with optional parameters, which can lead to unexpected type checking behavior.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/typescript-website/blob/v2/packages/documentation/copy/en/handbook-v2/More on Functions.md#2025-04-20_snippet_17

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
function myForEach(arr: any[], callback: (arg: any, index?: number) => void) {
  for (let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
    callback(arr[i], i);
  }
}
```

