TITLE: Extracting Return Types with infer
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates creating a utility type that extracts the return type from function types using conditional types with the 'infer' keyword.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/typescript-website/blob/v2/packages/documentation/copy/en/handbook-v2/Type Manipulation/Conditional Types.md#2025-04-20_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
type GetReturnType<Type> = Type extends (...args: never[]) => infer Return
  ? Return
  : never;

type Num = GetReturnType<() => number>;
//   ^?

type Str = GetReturnType<(x: string) => string>;
//   ^?

type Bools = GetReturnType<(a: boolean, b: boolean) => boolean[]>;
//   ^?
```

