TITLE: Basic Indexed Access Type in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to access a specific property type from a defined type using bracket notation. This creates a new type that represents the type of the accessed property.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/typescript-website/blob/v2/packages/documentation/copy/en/handbook-v2/Type Manipulation/Indexed Access Types.md#2025-04-20_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
type Person = { age: number; name: string; alive: boolean };
type Age = Person["age"];
//   ^?
```

