TITLE: Handling Excess Property Checks in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates TypeScript's excess property checking mechanism and how it affects object literal assignments. The example shows how TypeScript catches potential errors when assigning object literals with extra properties.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/typescript-website/blob/v2/packages/documentation/copy/en/handbook-v2/Object Types.md#2025-04-20_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
interface SquareConfig {
  color?: string;
  width?: number;
}

function createSquare(config: SquareConfig): { color: string; area: number } {
  return {
    color: config.color || "red",
    area: config.width ? config.width * config.width : 20,
  };
}

let mySquare = createSquare({ colour: "red", width: 100 });
```

