TITLE: Working with Generic Array Types in TypeScript (Array Syntax)
DESCRIPTION: A generic function that works with arrays of a specific type, using the Type[] syntax. This allows accessing array properties like length while maintaining the generic typing for array elements.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/typescript-website/blob/v2/packages/documentation/copy/en/handbook-v2/Type Manipulation/Generics.md#2025-04-20_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
function loggingIdentity<Type>(arg: Type[]): Type[] {
  console.log(arg.length);
  return arg;
}
```

