TITLE: Type Narrowing with Null Checks in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to safely handle potentially null values by checking for null before accessing properties or methods, preventing runtime errors when strictNullChecks is enabled.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/typescript-website/blob/v2/packages/documentation/copy/en/handbook-v2/Everyday Types.md#2025-04-20_snippet_34

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
function doSomething(x: string | null) {
  if (x === null) {
    // do nothing
  } else {
    console.log("Hello, " + x.toUpperCase());
  }
}
```

