TITLE: Generic Class with String Type
DESCRIPTION: Shows how the same generic class can be used with string type, demonstrating type flexibility.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/typescript-website/blob/v2/packages/documentation/copy/en/handbook-v2/Type Manipulation/Generics.md#2025-04-20_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
let stringNumeric = new GenericNumber<string>();
stringNumeric.zeroValue = "";
stringNumeric.add = function (x, y) {
  return x + y;
};

console.log(stringNumeric.add(stringNumeric.zeroValue, "test"));
```

