TITLE: Using Readonly Properties in TypeScript Object Types
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the readonly modifier on object properties to prevent reassignment. The example shows that TypeScript will produce errors when attempting to write to readonly properties.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/typescript-website/blob/v2/packages/documentation/copy/en/handbook-v2/Object Types.md#2025-04-20_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
interface SomeType {
  readonly prop: string;
}

function doSomething(obj: SomeType) {
  // We can read from 'obj.prop'.
  console.log(`prop has the value '${obj.prop}'.`);

  // But we can't re-assign it.
  obj.prop = "hello";
}
```

