TITLE: Creating Type Aliases for Union Types
DESCRIPTION: A simple example showing how to create a type alias for a union type. The ID type aliases the union of number | string for more readable type annotations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/typescript-website/blob/v2/packages/documentation/copy/en/handbook-v2/Everyday Types.md#2025-04-20_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
type ID = number | string;
```

