TITLE: Implementing Generic Class in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates creating a generic class that can work with different types. Shows usage with both number and string types.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/typescript-website/blob/v2/packages/documentation/copy/en/handbook-v2/Type Manipulation/Generics.md#2025-04-20_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
class GenericNumber<NumType> {
  zeroValue: NumType;
  add: (x: NumType, y: NumType) => NumType;
}

let myGenericNumber = new GenericNumber<number>();
myGenericNumber.zeroValue = 0;
myGenericNumber.add = function (x, y) {
  return x + y;
};
```

