TITLE: Defining Type Aliases for Object Types
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates creating a type alias for an object type and using it in a function parameter. The Point type defines a structure with x and y number properties.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/typescript-website/blob/v2/packages/documentation/copy/en/handbook-v2/Everyday Types.md#2025-04-20_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
type Point = {
  x: number;
  y: number;
};

// Exactly the same as the earlier example
function printCoord(pt: Point) {
  console.log("The coordinate's x value is " + pt.x);
  console.log("The coordinate's y value is " + pt.y);
}

printCoord({ x: 100, y: 100 });
```

