TITLE: Declaring Class Fields with Type Annotations
DESCRIPTION: Defines a Point class with x and y fields that have explicit number type annotations. This demonstrates how to add typed properties to a class.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/typescript-website/blob/v2/packages/documentation/copy/en/handbook-v2/Classes.md#2025-04-20_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// @strictPropertyInitialization: false
class Point {
  x: number;
  y: number;
}

const pt = new Point();
pt.x = 0;
pt.y = 0;
```

