TITLE: ES Module Format Example
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates ES module format usage with various import styles and exports.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/typescript-website/blob/v2/packages/documentation/copy/en/modules-reference/Reference.md#2025-04-20_snippet_19

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// @Filename: main.ts
import x, { y, z } from "mod";
import * as mod from "mod";
const dynamic = import("mod");
console.log(x, y, z, mod, dynamic);

export const e1 = 0;
export default "default export";
```

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// @Filename: main.js
import x, { y, z } from "mod";
import * as mod from "mod";
const dynamic = import("mod");
console.log(x, y, z, mod, dynamic);

export const e1 = 0;
export default "default export";
```

