TITLE: Creating Generic Object Types in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet introduces generic object types using a Box interface as an example. It shows how to define a generic interface and use it with different types.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/typescript-website/blob/v2/packages/documentation/copy/en/handbook-v2/Object Types.md#2025-04-20_snippet_21

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
interface Box<Type> {
  contents: Type;
}

let box: Box<string>;

let boxA: Box<string> = { contents: "hello" };
boxA.contents;

let boxB: StringBox = { contents: "world" };
boxB.contents;
```

