TITLE: Null Checking in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Shows how TypeScript narrows types when checking for null values. The 'printAll' function demonstrates handling of string, string array, and null types.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/typescript-website/blob/v2/packages/documentation/copy/en/handbook-v2/Narrowing.md#2025-04-20_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
function printAll(strs: string | string[] | null) {
  if (strs !== null) {
    if (typeof strs === "object") {
      for (const s of strs) {
        //            ^?
        console.log(s);
      }
    } else if (typeof strs === "string") {
      console.log(strs);
      //          ^?
    }
  }
}
```

