TITLE: Defining and Using Union Types in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines a function that accepts a union type (number | string) and demonstrates valid and invalid parameter values. It shows how TypeScript enforces type checking for union types.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/typescript-website/blob/v2/packages/documentation/copy/en/handbook-v2/Everyday Types.md#2025-04-20_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// @errors: 2345
function printId(id: number | string) {
  console.log("Your ID is: " + id);
