TITLE: Implementing Disposable Interface in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to implement the Disposable interface to create a disposable resource. It shows the implementation of a TraceActivity class with a dispose method.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/typescript-website/blob/v2/packages/documentation/copy/en/reference/Variable Declarations.md#2025-04-20_snippet_28

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
interface Disposable {
  [Symbol.dispose](): void;
}

class TraceActivity implements Disposable {
  readonly name: string;
  constructor(name: string) {
    this.name = name;
    console.log(`Entering: ${name}`);
  }

  [Symbol.dispose](): void {
    console.log(`Exiting: ${name}`);
  }
}

function f() {
  using _activity = new TraceActivity("f");
  console.log("Hello world!");
}

f();
// prints:
//   Entering: f
//   Hello world!
//   Exiting: f
```

