TITLE: Switch(true) Type Narrowing Example
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates TypeScript's ability to narrow types based on conditions in case clauses within a switch(true) statement.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/typescript-website/blob/v2/packages/documentation/copy/en/release-notes/TypeScript 5.3.md#2025-04-20_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
function f(x: unknown) {
    switch (true) {
        case typeof x === "string":
            // 'x' is a 'string' here
            console.log(x.toUpperCase());
            // falls through...

        case Array.isArray(x):
            // 'x' is a 'string | any[]' here.
            console.log(x.length);
            // falls through...

        default:
          // 'x' is 'unknown' here.
          // ...
    }
}
```

