TITLE: Non-null and Non-undefined Type Guards in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how type guards are extended to support non-null and non-undefined checks in TypeScript 2.0. It shows how the compiler handles type narrowing in conditional statements.
