TITLE: Preserve Module Format Example
DESCRIPTION: Example of preserve module format which maintains both ECMAScript imports and CommonJS require statements.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/typescript-website/blob/v2/packages/documentation/copy/en/modules-reference/Reference.md#2025-04-20_snippet_18

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// @Filename: main.ts
import x, { y, z } from "mod";
import mod = require("mod");
const dynamic = import("mod");

export const e1 = 0;
export default "default export";
```

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// @Filename: main.js
import x, { y, z } from "mod";
const mod = require("mod");
const dynamic = import("mod");

export const e1 = 0;
export default "default export";
```

